<item>
            <title>[JXPATH-172] Clarify JavaDoc of JXPathContext#getPointer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JXPATH-172</link>
                <project id="12310480" key="JXPATH">Commons JXPath</project>
                    <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Traverses the xpath and returns a Pointer. A Pointer provides easy access to a property. If the xpath matches no properties in the graph, the pointer will be null.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is not true because not &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; is returned but &lt;tt&gt;NullPointer&lt;/tt&gt;. This makes a tremendous difference.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12756928">JXPATH-172</key>
            <summary>Clarify JavaDoc of JXPathContext#getPointer</summary>
